roup with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "And myself, that was the trumpet section and Dizzy of course playing everything. Then you had Al McKibbon on bass, John Lewis was on piano and Specs Wright was on drums. Man, that was some band", "doc_title": "Gerald Wilson — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Wilson-Gerald/Gerald-Wilson_transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Junior Mance Part I", "relation": "toured with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "tour that is called “100 Gold Fingers,” it features ten piano players — Hank Jones, John Lewis, Kenny Barron... and myself.", "doc_title": "Junior Mance Part I interviewed by Monk Rowe and Michael Woods, New York City, New York, July 27, 1995 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/junior-mance-part-i-interviewed-monk-rowe-and-michael-woods-new-york-city-new"}, {"speaker": "Jones Hank", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "When John Lewis and I did this duo record that we did several years ago... John and I had known each other for some time", "doc_title": "Jones Hank — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Jones-Hank/Hank_Jones_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Dick Katz", "relation": "mentor of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Who became my mentor and dearest, dearest friend was John Lewis.", "doc_title": "Dick Katz interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 7, 2002", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/dick-katz-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-7-2002"}, {"speaker": "Kenny Clarke", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "So there I met John Lewis, and we began to play, and rehearse, and have fun playing music... Dizzy said, 'You're hired.' ... Which was John Lewis, Walter Fuller and Dizzy. We had three arrangers.", "doc_title": "52031_Kenny Clarke oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52031/"}, {"speaker": "Jim Hall", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I was involved in Oscar Peterson’s class... John Lewis had this School of Jazz... I got to be one of the teachers... John Lewis kept calling me... stay in my place.", "doc_title": "Jim Hall — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Hall-Jim/Jim-Hall_transcription.pdf"}]}